{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A static prompt-template lint check rejects phase-specific instruction leakage copied from SKILL.md.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is the lint rule logic over template text. No runtime harness, model call, or OS/network dependency is required to detect copied phase-instruction strings/patterns.","test_description":"Call the lint function on representative prompt templates (including one containing verbatim/near-verbatim phase instructions from SKILL.md) and assert it returns a violation with precise location/reason; assert clean templates pass.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The fully assembled prompt produced by the real test harness (after interpolation/fixtures) still contains no phase-instruction leakage.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real risk is introduced by composition/interpolation across modules and fixtures. A unit test of the linter alone can miss leakage injected during assembly.","test_description":"Run the actual prompt-builder/harness path with real fixtures and interpolation inputs, capture the final assembled prompt string, and assert no forbidden phase-instruction snippets/patterns are present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The test invocation loads skill context from the plugin/skill files and validates behavior from that context rather than from hard-coded prompt rules.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This depends on wiring between test invocation, skill-loader, and filesystem-backed skill/plugin assets. In-process mocks can hide path/config/load regressions.","test_description":"Execute the test invocation through the real loader against actual plugin/skill files, then assert provenance: loaded skill content is present in assembled context and no hard-coded phase rules are injected by test code.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If the relevant SKILL.md section is removed or degraded, the behavioral test fails with the same user-style prompt.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness claim is that behavior quality changes when real skill context changes under the same user prompt. That relies on real model behavior and can vary run-to-run; mocks would mask this.","test_description":"Run the same behavioral test prompt against (a) intact skill content and (b) intentionally degraded/removed target SKILL.md section using the real model path; require pass on (a) and fail on (b) under defined acceptance thresholds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.16}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Raw model output is captured to a diagnostic artifact before any JSON parsing or extraction logic runs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Ordering and data-flow across model-call, artifact writing, and parser stages must be validated together. Unit tests can miss pipeline sequencing bugs.","test_description":"Invoke the real response-handling pipeline with a response that later fails parsing; assert raw output artifact is written first and preserved even when parsing/extraction throws.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Assertions verify structured behavior (for example field placement or schema shape), not mere keyword presence that could come from prompt echoing.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure is weak assertion strategy in behavioral tests. You need assertion logic + harness outputs together, including adversarial echoed-keyword outputs, but not necessarily a real LLM call.","test_description":"Feed test assertions with outputs that contain expected keywords but wrong structure, and outputs with correct schema/field placement; assert failures for keyword-only echoes and passes only for structurally valid outputs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0}}]}
